cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is about evaluating probabilistic topic modeling algorithms in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves statistical analysis and machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of synthetic corpora, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
